---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About 50 Beautiful Places"
  description="Learn about the editorial approach behind 50 Beautiful Places, a lightweight travel inspiration site built with Astro."
>
  <section class="page-hero compact">
    <p class="eyebrow">About the project</p>
    <h1>A calm, maintainable travel guide library.</h1>
    <p>
      50 Beautiful Places is structured for image-led destination stories with practical notes,
      clean metadata, static pages, and a publishing workflow that respects Netlify build minutes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-narrow prose">
    <h2>Editorial approach</h2>
    <p>
      The site favors concise guides that help readers decide where to go and what kind of trip a place rewards.
      New destinations can be added as Markdown files in the Astro content collection.
    </p>
    <h2>Publishing approach</h2>
    <p>
      During heavy iteration, build and preview locally before using Netlify CLI previews. Push stable grouped commits
      to GitHub when the work is ready for an automatic Netlify production build.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
